msgstr "Vaikimisi: 1"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Default character set used by the client's kernel. In this case the "
"<option>iocharset</option> option is omitted from the command line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2162 index.docbook:2756
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2165 index.docbook:2759
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-1:1998. This character-encoding scheme is used throughout the "
"Americas, Western Europe, Oceania, and much of Africa."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2170 index.docbook:2764
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-2"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2173 index.docbook:2767
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-2:1999. It is informally referred to as \"Latin-2\". It is "
"generally intended for Central or \"Eastern European\" languages that are "
"written in the Latin script."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2178 index.docbook:2772
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-3"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2181 index.docbook:2775
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-3:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin-3 or South "
"European. It was designed to cover Turkish, Maltese and Esperanto, though "
"the introduction of ISO/IEC 8859-9 superseded it for Turkish."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2186 index.docbook:2780
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-4"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2189 index.docbook:2783
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-4:1998. It is informally referred to as Latin-4 or North "
"European. It was designed to cover Estonian, Latvian, Lithuanian, "
"Greenlandic, and Sami. It has been largely superseded by ISO/IEC 8859-10 and "
"Unicode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2194 index.docbook:2788
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-5"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2197 index.docbook:2791
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-5:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin/Cyrillic. It was "
"designed to cover languages using a Cyrillic alphabet such as Bulgarian, "
"Belarusian, Russian, Serbian and Macedonian but was never widely used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2202 index.docbook:2796
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-6"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2205 index.docbook:2799
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-6:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin/Arabic. It was "
"designed to cover Arabic."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2210 index.docbook:2804
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-7"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2213 index.docbook:2807
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-7:2003. It is informally referred to as Latin/Greek. It was "
"designed to cover the modern Greek language."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2218 index.docbook:2812
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-8"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2221 index.docbook:2815
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-8:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin/Hebrew. ISO/IEC "
"8859-8 covers all the Hebrew letters, but no Hebrew vowel signs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2226 index.docbook:2820
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-9"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2229 index.docbook:2823
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-9:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin-5 or Turkish. It "
"was designed to cover the Turkish language, designed as being of more use "
"than the ISO/IEC 8859-3 encoding."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2234 index.docbook:2828
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-13"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2237 index.docbook:2831
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-13:1998. It is informally referred to as Latin-7 or Baltic Rim. "
"It was designed to cover the Baltic languages, and added characters used in "
"the Polish language missing from the earlier encodings ISO 8859-4 and ISO "
"8859-10. Unlike these two, it does not cover the Nordic languages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2242 index.docbook:2836
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-14"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2245 index.docbook:2839
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-14:1998. It is informally referred to as Latin-8 or Celtic. It "
"was designed to cover the Celtic languages, such as Irish, Manx, Scottish "
"Gaelic, Welsh, Cornish, and Breton."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2250 index.docbook:2844
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-15"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2253 index.docbook:2847
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-15:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin-9 (and for a "
"while Latin-0). It is similar to ISO 8859-1, and thus also intended for "
"“Western European” languages, but replaces some less common symbols with the "
"euro sign and some letters that were deemed necessary."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2258 index.docbook:2852
#, no-c-format
msgid "utf8"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2261 index.docbook:2855
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Unicode (or Universal Coded Character Set) Transformation Format – 8-bit. "
"UTF-8 is used by many &Linux; distributions as default character set, and "
"is, in addition, by far the most common encoding for the World Wide Web."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2266 index.docbook:2860
#, no-c-format
msgid "koi8-r"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2269 index.docbook:2863
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KOI8-R (RFC 1489) is an 8-bit character encoding, derived from the KOI-8 "
"encoding by the programmer Andrei Chernov in 1993 and designed to cover "
"Russian, which uses a Cyrillic alphabet."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2274 index.docbook:2868
#, no-c-format
msgid "koi8-u"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2277 index.docbook:2871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KOI8-U (RFC 2319) is an 8-bit character encoding, designed to cover "
"Ukrainian, which uses a Cyrillic alphabet."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2282 index.docbook:2876
#, no-c-format
msgid "koi8-ru"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2285 index.docbook:2879
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KOI8-RU is an 8-bit character encoding, designed to cover Russian, "
"Ukrainian, and Belarusian which use a Cyrillic alphabet."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2290 index.docbook:2884 index.docbook:3135
#, no-c-format
msgid "cp1251"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2293 index.docbook:2887
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Windows-1251 is an 8-bit character encoding, designed to cover languages "
"that use the Cyrillic script such as Russian, Bulgarian, Serbian Cyrillic "
"and other languages. In Linux, the encoding is known as cp1251."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2298 index.docbook:2892
#, no-c-format
msgid "gb2312"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2301 index.docbook:2895
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"GB/T 2312-1980 is a key official character set of the People's Republic of "
"China, used for Simplified Chinese characters. GB2312 is the registered "
"internet name for EUC-CN, which is its usual encoded form. GB/T 2312-1980 "
"has been superseded by GBK and GB18030, which include additional characters, "
"but GB/T 2312 remains in widespread use as a subset of those encodings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2306 index.docbook:2900
#, no-c-format
msgid "big5"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2309 index.docbook:2903
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Big-5 or Big5 is a Chinese character encoding method used in Taiwan, Hong "
"Kong, and Macau for traditional Chinese characters. The People's Republic of "
"China (PRC), which uses simplified Chinese characters, uses the GB 18030 "
"character set instead."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2314 index.docbook:2908
#, no-c-format
msgid "euc-jp"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2317 index.docbook:2911
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"EUC-JP is a variable-width encoding used to represent the elements of three "
"Japanese character set standards, namely JIS X 0208, JIS X 0212, and JIS X "
"0201."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2322 index.docbook:2916
#, no-c-format
msgid "euc-kr"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2325 index.docbook:2919
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"EUC-KR is a variable-width encoding to represent Korean text using two coded "
"character sets, KS X 1001 (formerly KS C 5601) and either ISO 646:KR (KS X "
"1003, formerly KS C 5636) or US-ASCII, depending on variant. KS X 2901 "
"(formerly KS C 5861) stipulates the encoding and RFC 1557 dubbed it as EUC-"
"KR."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2330 index.docbook:2924
#, no-c-format
msgid "tis-620"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2333 index.docbook:2927
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Thai Industrial Standard 620-2533, commonly referred to as TIS-620, is the "
"most common character set and character encoding for the Thai language."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2337
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<guimenu>Search</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Clear</guimenuitem>"
msgid "Default: not selected; CHARSET: <guimenuitem>default</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Otsing</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Puhasta</guimenuitem>"

